reviewText: I truly am amazed at the good reviews on this film!  It saddens me so  much that people can relate positively to a story filled with nothing but numbskull idiots bent on making one foolish decision after the other.  If it were only a slapstick modern version of the three stooges it would be one thing but I perceive that folks actually WANT to relate to these types! I stand dumbfounded!

reviewText: I just happened to pick up "Paper Soldiers" one day while at the video store, not knowing exactly what to think of it. When I took it home and watched it, I was pleasantly surprised. This film is seriously funny!The film centers around Shawn, who is on parole and trying to get the almighty dollar fast. The film follows him through his adventures with breaking and entering, yet trying to keep his life on track. It'll have you rolling!Since the film was directed by Damon Dash, CEO of Roc-A-Fella records, the film is filled with cameos by Jay-Z, Memphis Bleek, and Dash himself. Beanie Siegel also gives a convincing performance as a crazy and extremely violent acquaintance of Shawn's. Angie Martinez, Tiffany Withers (from BET's bet.com), and Stacy Dash also have roles in the filmDon't let the fact that this is a straight-to-video film. It is very funny and I know you'll enjoy it!!!!

reviewText: I have to admit that I also LMAO!Hubby came home telling me that he had a movie with members from the ROC and I was very skeptical especially after viewing State Property (((YUCK)))Kevin Hart has an annoying voice, but he is semi funny as he pokes fun at himself!Vicariously seen through the eyes of Shawn a parolee who is desperate to just try keep the electric and gas running and his son off the bowls of cereal at night. As his options are none he decides to go into B&E; with his eccentric crew!I'm telling you Capone, Beanie, Damon Dash and Memphis Bleek had me crying! I didn't see the point of Stacy Dash, but I loved Tiffany and Angie in here.Funny movie...
